Adds a webhook and persistent GCP worker for incremental indexing

- Creates a secure webhook server on Cloud Run to receive GitHub push events.
- Publishes events to a GCP Pub/Sub topic to decouple the webhook from the worker.
- Implements a persistent worker on a GCP Compute Engine VM to handle large repositories efficiently.
- Updates the `setup` command to `git pull` existing repos, ensuring code is always current.
- Adds a `--log-mode` flag to the `incremental-index` command for better logging in a server environment.
- Upgrades the project's required Node.js version to ">=20" to support modern dependencies.
- Fixes module resolution errors by switching from barrel file imports to direct imports.
- Creates a comprehensive deployment guide for the new GCP architecture, including local testing instructions.
- Updates deployment guide to use Artifact Registry instead of the deprecated Container Registry.

